<div id="main_content">
	<h2>Hurricane Relief Efforts</h2>
	
	<p class="article_info">
		
			By UCF Staff
		
		<span class="date">Updated Nov. 2, 2005</span></p>
	
	
	
		<div class="article_img" style="width: px;">

			<img alt="Article Main Picture" src="../resources/sites/UCF/content/live/NEWS/0/NE554/en_US/Relief.jpg" height="" width=""  /> 
			
				<p class="photo_credit">Photo: Troy Williamson</p>
			
			<p>UCF Police package donations to send to hurricane victims in the north Gulf Coast.</p>
			
				<p class="note"><a class="full_photo" id="popup.jsp?article_id=002400411a428d50103c2675a02005d4c">Full Photo</a></p>
			
			
			
			
					
						
						
							
								<h3>Story Images</h3>
								<ul id="story_images">
							
						<li>
						<a class="full_photo" id="popup.jsp?article_id=002400411a428d50103c2675a02005d4c&amp;img_mode=1&amp;index=0">
							<img width="100" alt="Article Main Picture" src="../resources/sites/UCF/content/live/NEWS/0/NE554/en_US/Relief2.jpg"  />
						</a>
						</li>
						
						
					
			
			
			
					
						
						
						
					
			
			
			</ul><p  class="note">Click thumbnails for full-size images.</p>
		</div>
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
		
			<div id="related">
				<h3>Related Contacts and Links:</h3>
				<ul>
		
		<li>
		
			
				<h4><a href="mailto:tevelyn@mail.ucf.edu">Tom Evelyn</a></h4>
			
			
			
				<ul>
				<li>407-823-5988</li>
			
			</ul>
		
		</li>
	
	
	
		
		<li>
		
			<h4><a href="index?page=article&amp;id=002400411a428d50103c2675a02005947">UCF Enrolls Dozens of College Students Displaced by Hurricane Katrina</a></h4>
		
		</li>
	
	
	 </ul></div> 
	
	
			
	
	
	
	
		
	
	
		
	
	
		
	
	
		
	
	
		
	
	
		
	
	<div id="share">
		<ul><li><p id="print"><a href="javascript:window.print();">Print this Page</a></li></ul>
	
	</div>
	
	
	
	
		
			<p>The <place /><placetype />University</placetype /> of <placename />Central Florida</placename /></place /> community is working through various fund-raisers and relief efforts to help students and residents of the <place /><placetype />Gulf</placetype /> <placetype />Coast</placetype /></place /> region who have been affected by the devastation of hurricanes Katrina and Rita.</p><p /><p /><p>In addition to these efforts, the university allowed <a href="index?page=article&amp;id=002400411a428d50103c2675a02005947">students who were displaced by Hurricane Katrina to register</a> at UCF. Admissions staff members worked one-on-one with the displaced students to expedite admission, enrollment and financial assistance. UCF also will work with the students to help them return to their home institutions when they re-open.</p><p>Donations for relief efforts can be made directly to the American Red Cross by calling 1-800-HELP NOW (1-800-435-7669) or through the Red Cross Web site: <a href="http://www.redcross.org/">www.redcross.org</a>. The Salvation Army Web site -- <a href="http://www.salvationarmyusa.org/">www.salvationarmyusa.org</a> -- provides information on donating online, by phone and locally. </p><p /><p /><p><strong>Following are various efforts by the UCF community</strong> to help those who are in need. This list cant possibly include every effort and is not an endorsement by the university. Please donate or help as you see fit.</p><p /><p /><p /><p>-- The Recreation and <place /><placename />Wellness</placename /> <placetype />Center</placetype /></place /> will hold a sand volleyball tournament at the RWC courts on Nov. 18 with part of the proceeds going to hurricane aid. Contact Erin Alexander at <u><a href="mailto:ucfrec@mail.ucf.edu">ucfrec@mail.ucf.edu</a></u> for more information. </p><p /><p>-- The <a href="http://ucfathletics.collegesports.com/sports/w-volley/ucf-w-volley-body.html">UCF volleyball team</a> is collecting donations for <a href="http://national.unitedway.org/">United Way</a> relief efforts before each home match this season at the UCF Arena.</p><p /><p /><p /><p /><p /><p /><p /><p>-- <a href="http://police.ucf.edu/">UCF Police</a> are accepting donations for the American Red Cross or the Salvation Army (checks only, made payable to the relief agency). The department also spent two days loading two vehicles and a trailer full of relief supplies donated by students, staff and faculty. The donations were delivered to hurricane victims along the Gulf Coast<state /><place /></place /></state />.</p><p /><p><span></span></p><p /><p /><p /><p /><p /><p /><p /><p /><p>-- The <a href="http://www.ncfs.ucf.edu/home.html"><place /><placename />National</placename /> <placetype />Center</placetype /></place /> for Forensic Science</a> is collecting checks for the American Red Cross. Those interested in donating can drop off checks in Room 225M at the Partnership 1 building at 12354 Research Parkway.</p><p /><p /><p>-- The <a href="http://pegasus.cc.ucf.edu/~uspsstaf/">Staff Council</a> is collecting donations for the Salvation Army and American Red Cross. Call Joanne McCully at 407-823-6178.</p><p /><p /><p>-- The UCF chapter of <a href="http://www.mmae.engr.ucf.edu/~seds/">SEDS</a>, or Students for the Exploration and Development of Space, has been collecting money from its members for the American Red Cross. </p><p /><p>-- <a href="http://cdws.ucf.edu/">Course Development and Web Services</a> is accepting donations (checks only, made payable to the American Red Cross). </p><p /><p /><p /><p /><p /><p /><p /><p /><p /><p /><p>-- The UCF French Department in the <a href="http://www.cas.ucf.edu/forlang/main.php?page=home">Department for Modern Languages and Literatures</a> is working with the French Honor Society and other organizations to collect food and other items for <city /><place />New Orleans</place /></city /> residents. A collection point for the following items has been set up in Colbourn Hall 514: water, peanut butter (plastic jar), jelly (plastic jar), snack packs, fruit packs, snack bars, cereal bars, canned tuna, canned chicken, mints, baby food, diapers (size 3 and up), formula and cookies. The group is also collecting silverware set packets (individually wrapped like you get at a restaurant), any non-perishable food item that does not have to be opened with a can opener and is not in a glass container, personal hygiene items, toothbrushes, toothpaste and deodorant.</p><p /><p /><p>-- The Association for Doctoral Students in Exceptional Education has provided a box for clothing donations in the <place /><placename />Education</placename /> <placetype />Building</placetype /></place /> lobby. </p><p /><p /><p /><p /><p /><p /><p>-- Student organizations in the <a href="http://www.cohpa.ucf.edu/index.cfm"><place /><placetype />College</placetype /> of <placename />Health</placename /></place /> and Public Affairs</a> are raising money and collecting toiletries, clothes and other items for the relief effort. Call 407-823-2723 for more information.</p><p /><p /><p /><p>-- <a href="http://www.admissions.sdes.ucf.edu/">Undergraduate Admissions</a> has been collecting money to donate to the American Red Cross.</p><p /><p /><p>-- <a href="http://www.cohpa.ucf.edu/nursing/">Nursing</a> student Danielle Snelling is collecting clothing and shoes for men, women and children to help the families of shipping and oil workers who were affected by the hurricane.</p><p /><p /><p>-- Richard Lapchick, chair of the <a href="http://www.bus.ucf.edu/sport/cgi-bin/site/sitew.cgi">DeVos Sport Business Management Program</a> and director of the Institute for Diversity and Ethics in Sport and National Consortium for Academics and Sports, is matching donations from students, faculty and NCAS staff.</p><p /><p /><p>-- The <a href="http://pegasus.cc.ucf.edu/~wpb2001/wpb.html">Womens Prayer Band</a> at UCF is gathering clothing to donate. Call 407-294-5487 for more information.</p><p /><p /><p /><p>-- <a href="http://pegasus.cc.ucf.edu/~circlek/">Circle K International of UCF</a> has been collecting donations and supplies in front of the Student Union to send to the American Red Cross. The South Orlando Kiwanis Club will deliver the supplies to <state /><place />Louisiana</place /></state />.</p><p /><p /><p /><p /><p>-- The <place /><placename /><a href="http://www.fsec.ucf.edu/">Florida</placename /> <placename />Solar</placename /> <placename />Energy</placename /> <placetype />Center</a></placetype /></place /> is coordinating solar energy support between the solar industry and disaster organizations to help provide power at shelters, homes and other facilities.</p><p /><p /><p>-- <a href="http://victimservices.ucf.edu/">Victim Services</a> will donate all funds raised in September as part of its ongoing cell phone donation program to the American Red Cross for their support and assistance to victims of Hurricane Katrina.</p><p /><p /><p /><p /><p><em>(UCF homepage &quot;Spotlight&quot; photo: FEMA)</em></p>
		
	
	<p id="back"><a href="index?page=news">&lt; Back to the Newsroom</a></p>

